The paper deals with the problem of automatically inserting synchronization primitives in multithreaded programs to ensure correctness, and optimizing the solution quality to meet quantitative objectives such as program performance. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), distributed computing (cs.DC), computer architecture (cs.AR), and systems and control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.PL and cs.SE are the most likely categories as they deal with program correctness and optimization.
